&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position: &lt;/strong&gt;Commercial Development Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Sales&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;OEM /CGS Sales&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;UK preferred, other locations in EU near major airports considered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; BS with 5 - 10 years relevant experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Watchmaker is inviting applications for the full-time position of Commercial Development Manager, based in western Europe. This position reports to the Vice President of Commercial Development and will be responsible for driving sales growth via OEM partnerships across the company’s genomics product portfolio with an emphasis on NGS solutions and engineered enzyme systems for diagnostic applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced working environment and contribute directly to our company culture and success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position provides an opportunity to expand relationships with existing partners, as well as develop new Watchmaker commercial partnerships with cutting-edge technology developers driving exciting new applications in a rapidly evolving industry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain existing accounts and relationships within the segment. Build relationships with customer product development teams to secure business continuity through new iterations of customer products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand business at existing accounts through a keen understanding of NGS&amp;nbsp; &amp;amp; Molecular Diagnostic workflows and assays, including and associated enzymology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate contact with new prospects to understand priorities,&amp;nbsp; identify pain points and develop strategies to address prospects’ business needs, building long term relationships to enable Watchmaker early access to evolving assay development requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Astutely deliver Watchmaker’s strong value proposition to new prospects via in person meetings and video conferences - both conversationally and with custom tailored presentations to communicate key differentiators based on customer needs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a territory business plan including strategic target account priorities to penetrate and establish new key accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate key trends in the market and industry and provide feedback on lucrative portfolio expansion opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
