&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and implement Watchmaker’s APAC sales strategy across direct and distributor markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key countries to focus and grow initially include: China, S. Korea, Japan, Australia, India&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop the APAC commercial team, partnering with the existing in-region team and adding new direct hires over time; ensure the team is motivated, mentored, incentivized, and retained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, develop, and manage international distribution channels across APAC markets including Greater China, Japan, South Korea, Southeast Asia, ANZ, and India; provide sales, marketing, and customer support as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish relationships with KOL’s and key customers in the regions (leading Genome sequencing centers, services providers and translational laboratories utilizing NGS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage Commercial Operations and analytics to accurately forecast and implement operational plans to drive revenue growth across the region&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and respond to APAC market dynamics to drive market development and expansion strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate appropriately with the Executive team, Marketing, R&amp;amp;D, Finance, Product Management, and Commercial Operations to translate regional customer feedback into current and future products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate sales and marketing campaigns across APAC markets to ensure rapid increase in regional sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the APAC sales budget; set quarterly and annual sales goals by collaborating with Finance and Commercial Operations teams&lt;/li&gt;
