&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Vice President, Marketing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full Time&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Marketing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Boulder Colorado preferred, open to remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;Masters with 15+ years of experience and 5 years of experience leading a team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Watchmaker is inviting applications for the full-time position of Vice President, Marketing based in Boulder, CO (open to remote).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced working environment and contribute directly to our company culture and success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Chief Commercial Officer, the VP of Marketing will lead and scale a high-performing team across Product Management, Product Marketing and Design, NPD Project Management and Product Operations. The VP will own the commercial marketing engine - product strategy, portfolio management, launches, brand, and revenue enablement. The organization is structured across four pillars: NGS Product Management, MDx/Enzymes Product Management, Product Operations and Product Marketing and Design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive product portfolio strategy across NGS, MDx/Enzymes, and emerging applications (In collaboration with R&amp;amp;D), in preparation for Portfolio Committee alignment, approval and prioritization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead commercial launch execution, ensuring campaigns, sales enablement, and customer engagement are ready&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly manage and develop the marketing organization across Product Management, Product Marketing and Design, NPD Project Management and Product Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the marketing leadership team to operate at leadership level through coaching, team development, and structural support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Portfolio Committee proposal quality with commercial depth, competitive positioning, and strategic clarity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the Product Operations pillar including centralized pricing analysis, forecasting, marketing analytics, and PCQT coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead marketing strategy including positioning, messaging, campaigns, conferences, digital presence, and competitive intelligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the NPD Project management team, supporting the ELT and the company with portfolio and product level timelines and dashboards for on time, in full launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Chief Commercial Officer on commercial strategy, sales alignment, pricing, and revenue targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with R&amp;amp;D leadership on NPD pipeline, discovery priorities, product-market fit and 2-year rolling roadmaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive QBR cadence for portfolio health visibility and data-driven decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage marketing budget, headcount planning, and hiring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and leverage marketing automation tools and CRM to manage the funnel and drive conversions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and represent the company at key customer meetings, conferences, and industry events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: &lt;/strong&gt;The above responsibilities are not exhaustive and other similar duties may be required from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
